- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper introduces a novel formulation of discrete chaotic iterations in the field of dynamical systems and studies their topological properties. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper proposes a way to generate new hash functions using the chaotic behavior of the iterations. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the generation of hash functions, which is a topic related to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper studies the behavior of a system of discrete chaotic iterations and its properties. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical method for generating hash functions using chaotic iterations.
